<i>[LiSA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:03:18.831 --> 00:03:25.745
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:03:41.275 --> 00:03:42.612
<i>♪♪ I'm feeling magical ♪♪</i>

00:03:42.679 --> 00:03:45.752
<i>[LiSA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:03:45.818 --> 00:03:50.962
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:03:51.028 --> 00:03:54.001
<i>♪♪ I seen my hope ♪♪</i>
<i>[LiSA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:03:54.068 --> 00:03:59.579
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:03:59.646 --> 00:04:01.717
<i>♪♪ That's rising hope ♪♪</i>

00:04:01.784 --> 00:04:03.854
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:04:07.562 --> 00:04:10.701
[distant traffic noises]

00:04:13.039 --> 00:04:15.678
[Honoka] Okay, so it's Tatsuya
who keeps your CAD

00:04:15.745 --> 00:04:17.882
in working order.
Is that right, Miyuki?

00:04:17.949 --> 00:04:18.784
Yes.

00:04:18.851 --> 00:04:20.621
Having him do it
is the only thing

00:04:20.688 --> 00:04:22.424
that will put my mind at ease.

00:04:22.491 --> 00:04:24.563
I just make some
minor adjustments.

00:04:24.629 --> 00:04:25.798
‐ [Mizuki] That's true.
‐ [gasps]

00:04:25.865 --> 00:04:27.034
But you wouldn't be able
to do that

00:04:27.101 --> 00:04:28.838
unless you had the knowledge
to understand how

00:04:28.904 --> 00:04:30.207
the OS works, right?

00:04:30.273 --> 00:04:32.277
Besides that,
you also need the skills

00:04:32.344 --> 00:04:34.482
to access
the CAD's basic system.

00:04:34.549 --> 00:04:36.252
Pretty impressive.

00:04:36.319 --> 00:04:38.289
Hey Tatsuya,
mind taking a look at mine, too?

00:04:38.356 --> 00:04:39.593
Can't.

00:04:39.659 --> 00:04:41.997
A unique CAD like yours
is way to risky

00:04:42.064 --> 00:04:43.066
to mess around with.

00:04:43.133 --> 00:04:44.335
[chuckles]

00:04:44.401 --> 00:04:46.339
You really are as impressive
as they say.

00:04:46.874 --> 00:04:48.109
How so?

00:04:48.176 --> 00:04:50.915
The fact that you knew
right off that this was a CAD.

00:04:50.982 --> 00:04:51.917
[chuckles]

00:04:51.984 --> 00:04:53.052
Mm?

00:04:54.421 --> 00:04:55.958
[Leonhard] An
engraving‐type spell?

00:04:56.025 --> 00:04:57.161
[Erika] Right.

00:04:57.227 --> 00:04:59.533
That's why it's
all hollow except for the hilt.

00:04:59.599 --> 00:05:02.104
Meaning that you've got
to constantly feed it psions

00:05:02.171 --> 00:05:03.306
to keep working, right?

00:05:03.373 --> 00:05:05.243
How do you manage
to not run out of gas?

00:05:05.310 --> 00:05:07.281
Ah, so you know your field
of study.

00:05:07.347 --> 00:05:09.586
But sadly,
I'm not there yet.

00:05:09.653 --> 00:05:11.857
It won't use up too much
if I only transmit

00:05:11.924 --> 00:05:14.629
the psions at the moment
of extension and impact.

00:05:14.696 --> 00:05:16.567
It's like the helmet‐splitting
principle.

00:05:18.136 --> 00:05:19.371
Wait.

00:05:20.307 --> 00:05:21.677
What's wrong with you guys?

00:05:22.645 --> 00:05:24.014
‐ [Miyuki] Erika.
‐ Huh?

00:05:24.081 --> 00:05:27.020
I think helmet‐splitting
is a technique categorized

00:05:27.087 --> 00:05:29.626
under secret skills
or the arcane arts,

00:05:29.693 --> 00:05:32.866
but it's way more than a matter
of having tons of psions.

00:05:32.932 --> 00:05:36.305
Maybe the more likely truth
of it is that regular civilians

00:05:36.372 --> 00:05:38.076
are just a rarity at our school.

00:05:38.443 --> 00:05:40.046
I don't believe there
are any civilians

00:05:40.113 --> 00:05:41.349
at Magic High School.

00:05:42.017 --> 00:05:43.152
[all gasping]

00:05:43.219 --> 00:05:44.756
[Leonhard] Yeah.

00:05:49.498 --> 00:05:50.668
[Mayumi] Tatsuya!

00:05:55.343 --> 00:05:56.613
Morning, Tatsuya.

00:05:57.147 --> 00:05:59.385
And a very good morning
to you, too, Miyuki.

00:06:00.287 --> 00:06:01.890
Yes, good morning, President.

00:06:01.957 --> 00:06:03.059
Thanks.

00:06:03.426 --> 00:06:05.030
Good morning to you, ma'am.

00:06:05.531 --> 00:06:06.633
There's something I'd like

00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:08.604
to discuss with you later,
Miyuki.

00:06:09.038 --> 00:06:10.841
What are your plans
for lunch this afternoon?

00:06:10.908 --> 00:06:11.977
Are you free?

00:06:15.483 --> 00:06:16.653
[exhales]

00:06:20.026 --> 00:06:21.162
[knocking]

00:06:21.229 --> 00:06:22.397
<i>[Mayumi] Come in!</i>

00:06:23.834 --> 00:06:24.803
Excuse me.

00:06:25.638 --> 00:06:27.341
Hello, welcome.

00:06:27.407 --> 00:06:29.846
Come on in.
Don't be shy.

00:06:34.856 --> 00:06:36.492
Excuse me.

00:06:38.162 --> 00:06:39.733
[both gasping]

00:06:39.799 --> 00:06:41.837
‐ [clears throat]
‐ [gasps]

00:06:42.972 --> 00:06:44.743
[lunch boxes clattering]

00:06:46.747 --> 00:06:49.051
[Mayumi] I know we met
at the matriculation ceremony

00:06:49.118 --> 00:06:50.788
but just in case,

00:06:50.855 --> 00:06:55.397
next to me is our treasurer,
Suzune Ichihara, a. k. a. Rin.

00:06:55.463 --> 00:06:56.600
Actually, President,

00:06:56.667 --> 00:06:58.537
you're the only one
that calls me Rin.

00:06:58.604 --> 00:07:00.641
[Mayumi] Next to her
is Mari Watanabe,

00:07:00.708 --> 00:07:02.845
disciplinary committee
chairwoman.

00:07:02.912 --> 00:07:05.417
And that's our secretary,
Azusa Nakajou,

00:07:05.483 --> 00:07:06.452
or Ah‐chan.

00:07:06.520 --> 00:07:08.156
[grunts]
President!

00:07:08.222 --> 00:07:10.360
I beg of you,
please don't call me Ah‐chan

00:07:10.427 --> 00:07:12.097
in front of the underclassmen!

00:07:12.164 --> 00:07:14.803
I have a reputation to uphold,
too, you know.

00:07:14.869 --> 00:07:17.575
Plus Hanzo who is serving
as our vice president.

00:07:17.642 --> 00:07:19.512
Together the full
student council line up

00:07:19.579 --> 00:07:20.548
for this semester.

00:07:20.615 --> 00:07:22.250
Although I'm not a member.

00:07:22.685 --> 00:07:24.789
‐ [Miyuki] Miss Watanabe?
‐ What is it?

00:07:24.856 --> 00:07:27.361
Was that box lunch prepared
by someone else

00:07:27.427 --> 00:07:28.964
or did you make it yourself?

00:07:29.031 --> 00:07:30.066
I made it.

00:07:30.568 --> 00:07:31.770
Surprised?

00:07:31.837 --> 00:07:33.172
[Tatsuya] No, not at all.

00:07:33.239 --> 00:07:34.408
[gasps]

00:07:35.076 --> 00:07:37.247
We can tell by looking
at your hands, you see,

00:07:37.314 --> 00:07:39.184
how much regular cooking you do.

00:07:39.251 --> 00:07:41.489
[groans]

00:07:42.157 --> 00:07:43.126
I know!

00:07:43.192 --> 00:07:45.196
How about as of tomorrow,

00:07:45.263 --> 00:07:47.200
we bring box lunches also?

00:07:47.267 --> 00:07:49.238
Well, that does sound appealing.

00:07:49.706 --> 00:07:51.342
But we'll have no privacy.

00:07:51.409 --> 00:07:52.979
Honestly, you guys sound more

00:07:53.046 --> 00:07:54.749
like you're
a couple than siblings

00:07:54.816 --> 00:07:56.620
‐ [laughs]
‐ Oh, do we?

00:07:57.287 --> 00:07:58.857
Well, I must admit.

00:07:58.924 --> 00:07:59.826
[gasps]

00:07:59.893 --> 00:08:01.596
[Tatsuya] It has crossed
my mind

00:08:01.663 --> 00:08:03.634
that if we weren't related
by blood,

00:08:03.701 --> 00:08:06.272
we could very well be a couple.
True.

00:08:06.339 --> 00:08:07.474
[gasps]

00:08:08.076 --> 00:08:09.612
[all gasping]

00:08:12.484 --> 00:08:13.620
I'm joking,
of course.

00:08:13.687 --> 00:08:14.956
both: Huh?

00:08:15.558 --> 00:08:18.096
‐ Hmm?
‐ Uh, never mind.

00:08:18.964 --> 00:08:20.233
[whimpers]

00:08:21.035 --> 00:08:23.039
<i>[Miyuki] It's nothing.</i>
<i>Forget it.</i>

00:08:24.008 --> 00:08:25.778
[Mayumi] Why don't we get down
to business, then?

00:08:27.648 --> 00:08:29.451
At this school
the student council president

00:08:29.519 --> 00:08:30.788
is duly elected,

00:08:30.855 --> 00:08:33.560
but all of the other officers
are either chosen

00:08:33.627 --> 00:08:35.631
or dismissed
by the president alone.

00:08:35.698 --> 00:08:36.933
With few exceptions,

00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:38.937
the president also has
the power to appoint

00:08:39.004 --> 00:08:40.941
or release the chairman
of each committee.

00:08:41.008 --> 00:08:42.845
One such exception,
for example,

00:08:42.912 --> 00:08:44.916
would be my own
disciplinary committee.

00:08:44.983 --> 00:08:47.688
We appoint one officer each
to the student council,

00:08:47.755 --> 00:08:49.893
the extracurricular
activities federations,

00:08:49.959 --> 00:08:51.228
and the faculty committee,

00:08:51.295 --> 00:08:54.134
but the chairman is chosen
by an internal election.

00:08:54.201 --> 00:08:55.504
Hmm.

00:08:56.005 --> 00:08:59.779
Now, in keeping with our
school's annual tradition,

00:08:59.846 --> 00:09:01.850
it is now our pleasure
to appoint

00:09:01.917 --> 00:09:04.723
the first year representative
to the student council.

00:09:05.356 --> 00:09:09.098
Miyuki, I'd like you to be
the one who fulfills

00:09:09.164 --> 00:09:10.935
that esteemed role.

00:09:11.302 --> 00:09:12.872
Will you accept the appointment?

00:09:15.276 --> 00:09:16.278
[groans]

00:09:17.214 --> 00:09:18.249
[grunts]

00:09:19.485 --> 00:09:20.621
[grunts]

00:09:22.224 --> 00:09:23.226
Madam President,

00:09:23.292 --> 00:09:25.497
do you know about
my brother's exam scores?

00:09:25.564 --> 00:09:26.767
[gasps]

00:09:27.568 --> 00:09:30.373
If the council wants to recruit
a qualified individual,

00:09:30.440 --> 00:09:33.346
I believe my brother
is a far better choice than me.

00:09:34.014 --> 00:09:35.851
That the student council's
asking me

00:09:35.918 --> 00:09:38.189
to join their impressive ranks
honors me very deeply.

00:09:38.256 --> 00:09:39.526
Uh, hey, Miyuki.

00:09:39.592 --> 00:09:42.431
It would be my distinct pleasure
to join you at the foot

00:09:42.497 --> 00:09:44.234
of your table,
honestly,

00:09:44.301 --> 00:09:46.506
but is there any way that you
could bring my brother

00:09:46.573 --> 00:09:47.875
on board as well?

00:09:50.013 --> 00:09:52.451
‐ [all groaning]
‐ Unfortunately,

00:09:52.518 --> 00:09:54.121
that won't be possible.

00:09:54.188 --> 00:09:56.459
Officers of the student council
are chosen

00:09:56.526 --> 00:09:58.496
from among course one students.

00:09:58.564 --> 00:10:00.801
This is a respected precedent.

00:10:01.402 --> 00:10:02.738
[Suzune] To overturn this rule,

00:10:02.805 --> 00:10:04.776
the entire student body
would have to vote

00:10:04.843 --> 00:10:07.147
for an overhaul
of the system at large.

00:10:08.550 --> 00:10:10.621
[gasps]

00:10:11.590 --> 00:10:13.459
My sincere apologies, then.

00:10:13.527 --> 00:10:16.700
Please forgive me for being
so forward and so out of line.

00:10:17.869 --> 00:10:19.706
Let's see here.

00:10:19.772 --> 00:10:21.475
So are we agreed
that you'll officially

00:10:21.543 --> 00:10:23.246
be joining us and coming
on board

00:10:23.312 --> 00:10:26.252
as our new student council
secretary this semester, Miyuki?

00:10:27.154 --> 00:10:28.122
[grunts]

00:10:30.460 --> 00:10:31.830
[Miyuki] Yes.

00:10:31.897 --> 00:10:34.134
I'll do everything in my power
to serve you well,

00:10:34.201 --> 00:10:36.238
so please allow me to join you.

00:10:36.305 --> 00:10:37.407
[giggles]

00:10:37.474 --> 00:10:39.546
Ah‐chan will better explain
the particulars

00:10:39.612 --> 00:10:41.148
of your new duties.
Understood?

00:10:41.516 --> 00:10:42.685
[Mari] Can I jump in here?

00:10:42.752 --> 00:10:44.087
all: Huh?

00:10:44.421 --> 00:10:47.060
[Mari] There is one position
the disciplinary committee left

00:10:47.127 --> 00:10:48.831
by a graduate that has yet
to be filled

00:10:48.897 --> 00:10:50.133
by the student council.

00:10:50.200 --> 00:10:51.636
Yes,
but we're still going through

00:10:51.703 --> 00:10:53.674
the selection process.
I told you.

00:10:53.740 --> 00:10:55.243
If I'm not mistaken,

00:10:55.310 --> 00:10:57.949
selecting a course two student
as a student council nominee

00:10:58.015 --> 00:11:00.053
wouldn't violate any rules.
‐ [grunts]

00:11:01.455 --> 00:11:02.592
Isn't that true?

00:11:03.125 --> 00:11:04.796
‐ Great call!
‐ Huh?

00:11:05.163 --> 00:11:06.232
[Mayumi] For
the disciplinary committee,

00:11:06.298 --> 00:11:07.334
it's no problem!

00:11:07.400 --> 00:11:09.906
The council hereby nominates
Tatsuya Shiba

00:11:09.973 --> 00:11:11.877
to the disciplinary committee!

00:11:12.377 --> 00:11:13.881
Hold on a second, please.

00:11:13.947 --> 00:11:15.684
Do I have any say
in this decision?

00:11:15.751 --> 00:11:17.187
I mean,
in the first place,

00:11:17.254 --> 00:11:19.993
you haven't even explained to me
what this committee even does.

00:11:20.059 --> 00:11:22.965
Well, your sister'll have duties
on student council

00:11:23.032 --> 00:11:25.403
but we haven't told her what
those are yet, either.

00:11:26.540 --> 00:11:28.276
Well, yeah, that's true, but‐‐

00:11:28.342 --> 00:11:31.448
It'll be all right, Rin.
Just take it easy.

00:11:32.217 --> 00:11:35.356
Tatsuya, the disciplinary
committee maintains order

00:11:35.423 --> 00:11:36.392
at this school.

00:11:39.599 --> 00:11:41.101
[Tatsuya] Is that all they do?

00:11:41.168 --> 00:11:42.170
Pardon?

00:11:45.243 --> 00:11:46.680
[gasps]

00:11:47.480 --> 00:11:50.888
Well, um, there main duties
are to charge those in violation

00:11:50.955 --> 00:11:52.190
of the school
regulations regarding

00:11:52.257 --> 00:11:53.994
the use of magic
and to crack down

00:11:54.061 --> 00:11:56.198
on disorderly conduct involving
the same.

00:11:57.467 --> 00:12:00.206
Just in case,
I'd like to confirm one thing.

00:12:00.273 --> 00:12:01.676
Yes, what?

00:12:02.077 --> 00:12:03.780
[Tatsuya] If I
understand correctly,

00:12:03.847 --> 00:12:05.350
whenever a fight breaks out,

00:12:05.416 --> 00:12:07.888
the disciplinary committee has
to stop it by force.

00:12:07.955 --> 00:12:09.057
Is that right?

00:12:09.792 --> 00:12:11.195
Well, more or less.

00:12:11.262 --> 00:12:13.900
So then does that hold true
if any magic

00:12:13.967 --> 00:12:15.504
is being used whatsoever?

00:12:15.571 --> 00:12:19.044
Ideally, we'd manage to stop it
before they used any magic.

00:12:19.111 --> 00:12:23.019
Sorry, but I'm course two
because my practical exam scores

00:12:23.085 --> 00:12:24.454
were miserable.
‐ [Mari] That's fine.

00:12:24.522 --> 00:12:25.524
[grunts]

00:12:25.591 --> 00:12:26.793
We have me to deal

00:12:26.860 --> 00:12:28.129
with tests of strength.

00:12:29.064 --> 00:12:30.834
[school bell chimes]
[gasps]

00:12:30.901 --> 00:12:32.972
Right, let's pick this up again
after school.

00:12:33.039 --> 00:12:34.341
[Mari] That okay with you?

00:12:34.909 --> 00:12:36.011
[exhales sharply]

00:12:36.913 --> 00:12:38.249
[Tatsuya] Fine by me.

00:12:40.453 --> 00:12:41.455
[exhales]

00:12:51.876 --> 00:12:54.816
[magical chiming]

00:12:55.851 --> 00:12:57.087
[Leonhard]
Disciplinary committee?

00:12:57.153 --> 00:12:59.257
Yeah.
So anyway,

00:12:59.324 --> 00:13:01.997
I've gotta go discuss it
with them again after school.

00:13:02.063 --> 00:13:04.836
Well that sounds like
a giant pain in the ass.

00:13:04.902 --> 00:13:06.740
Isn't what
the disciplinary committee does

00:13:06.806 --> 00:13:08.175
kind of dangerous?

00:13:08.242 --> 00:13:10.748
Wow
She does what she wants.

00:13:11.248 --> 00:13:12.585
[Tatsuya] We're waiting, Erika.

00:13:12.652 --> 00:13:14.021
Uh, oh, yeah.
Sorry.

00:13:14.087 --> 00:13:16.091
But really,
what a load of B. S.

00:13:16.926 --> 00:13:18.295
Uh, Erika?

00:13:20.668 --> 00:13:23.540
[magical whooshing]

00:13:33.492 --> 00:13:34.494
Yes!

00:13:34.562 --> 00:13:37.467
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:13:37.535 --> 00:13:44.481
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:13:51.996 --> 00:13:53.099
<i>[Tatsuya] It's slow.</i>

00:13:59.311 --> 00:14:01.148
[groaning]

00:14:01.750 --> 00:14:03.419
<i>[Tatsuya] Too slow,</i>
<i>in fact.</i>

00:14:04.655 --> 00:14:06.025
<i>Come on.</i>

00:14:06.091 --> 00:14:08.396
<i>Is this really</i>
<i>the best I can do?</i>

00:14:11.001 --> 00:14:13.406
<i>I guess I don't belong here</i>
<i>after all.</i>

00:14:13.472 --> 00:14:14.509
[knocking]

00:14:14.575 --> 00:14:15.911
<i>Excuse us.</i>

00:14:18.950 --> 00:14:20.854
<i>I'll just politely decline.</i>

00:14:22.625 --> 00:14:24.294
It's Tatsuya Shiba.

00:14:24.595 --> 00:14:25.798
[Miyuki] And Miyuki Shiba.

00:14:25.864 --> 00:14:27.735
Hey, you made it.

00:14:28.169 --> 00:14:30.006
Hi, Miyuki.
Welcome.

00:14:30.373 --> 00:14:32.611
[Mayumi] And we're glad
you came, too, Tatsuya.

00:14:33.379 --> 00:14:35.016
[grunts]

00:14:44.669 --> 00:14:47.040
I'm Gyobu Hattori,
the vice president.

00:14:47.107 --> 00:14:49.244
We welcome you
to the student council, Miyuki.

00:14:49.311 --> 00:14:50.379
[grunts]

00:14:55.958 --> 00:14:58.229
Let's get started.
Ah‐chan, you're on.

00:14:58.597 --> 00:14:59.799
[grunts]
Right.

00:14:59.866 --> 00:15:01.435
[groans]

00:15:01.503 --> 00:15:03.640
Okay, why don't we get moving,
then?

00:15:03.707 --> 00:15:04.909
Where to?

00:15:04.976 --> 00:15:07.046
Disciplinary committee
headquarters.

00:15:07.113 --> 00:15:09.217
I suspect it would probably
be easier for you

00:15:09.284 --> 00:15:10.420
to watch and learn from there.

00:15:12.424 --> 00:15:14.695
[Gyobu] Miss Watanabe,
please wait a moment.

00:15:14.762 --> 00:15:15.931
‐ What is it...

00:15:16.398 --> 00:15:19.004
Vice president Hanzou
Gyobushoujo Hattori?

00:15:19.070 --> 00:15:21.108
I told you not to call me
by my full name!

00:15:21.175 --> 00:15:23.479
Fine, vice president
Hanzou Hattori.

00:15:23.547 --> 00:15:24.816
It's Gyobu Hattori!

00:15:24.882 --> 00:15:26.418
[Mari] But that's
a government post,

00:15:26.485 --> 00:15:28.122
not a name.
Isn't your family‐‐

00:15:28.189 --> 00:15:29.959
[Gyobu] We no longer hold
that office.

00:15:30.026 --> 00:15:32.397
At this school I'm registered
as Gyobu Hatto‐‐

00:15:32.698 --> 00:15:34.468
Wait, that's not the point.

00:15:34.836 --> 00:15:35.904
What's your problem?

00:15:36.973 --> 00:15:38.209
[grunts]

00:15:38.275 --> 00:15:39.779
[Gyobu] I disapprove
of this first year

00:15:39.846 --> 00:15:41.816
being appointed
to the disciplinary committee.

00:15:41.883 --> 00:15:46.325
No Weed has ever been assigned
that specific position.

00:15:46.826 --> 00:15:48.930
[Mari] It is forbidden to refer
to course two students

00:15:48.997 --> 00:15:49.999
as Weeds.

00:15:50.066 --> 00:15:51.135
You have some nerve to utter

00:15:51.201 --> 00:15:52.738
that term in front of me.

00:15:53.105 --> 00:15:55.511
Gloss it over all you want
but it does no good.

00:15:55.577 --> 00:15:56.546
Be honest.

00:15:56.613 --> 00:15:58.315
Do you intend to bust over
a third

00:15:58.382 --> 00:16:00.219
of the entire student body
for it?

00:16:00.621 --> 00:16:02.958
This committee's job
is to crack down on students

00:16:03.025 --> 00:16:05.731
in clear violation of the rules
using practical skills.

00:16:05.797 --> 00:16:08.235
[Gyobu] A Weed couldn't hack it.
They're too inferior.

00:16:08.302 --> 00:16:10.473
Yes, our system is merit‐based,

00:16:10.541 --> 00:16:12.945
but practical skills come
in many forms.

00:16:13.914 --> 00:16:15.617
Tatsuya has the eyesight
and brains

00:16:15.684 --> 00:16:17.555
to read activation
sequences directly,

00:16:17.621 --> 00:16:19.559
and he can accurately predict
which spell's about

00:16:19.625 --> 00:16:20.627
to be initiated.

00:16:20.694 --> 00:16:22.197
No way!

00:16:22.263 --> 00:16:24.134
Even an essential
singularity‐type

00:16:24.201 --> 00:16:26.205
activation sequence
is loaded with data,

00:16:26.271 --> 00:16:27.842
up to 30,000 letters.

00:16:27.908 --> 00:16:30.379
I refuse to believe you
could read it that quickly.

00:16:30.446 --> 00:16:32.483
Common sense tells us
there's no way.

00:16:32.551 --> 00:16:35.022
You're right, which is precisely
the reason his skills

00:16:35.089 --> 00:16:36.191
are so valuable.

00:16:36.258 --> 00:16:37.393
[Mari] I know.

00:16:37.460 --> 00:16:38.930
He's sure to be
a powerful deterrent

00:16:38.997 --> 00:16:40.466
towards all those
would‐be violators

00:16:40.534 --> 00:16:42.170
who keep getting off the hook,

00:16:42.237 --> 00:16:44.709
because we can never
fully establish their crimes.

00:16:44.775 --> 00:16:46.646
Anyway,
I have to admit,

00:16:46.713 --> 00:16:49.150
there's one more reason why
I want him on my committee.

00:16:49.217 --> 00:16:51.623
You see,
just as you keep on saying,

00:16:51.689 --> 00:16:54.595
there's an emotional chasm
between course one and two.

00:16:54.662 --> 00:16:56.666
[Mari] The course one
students insist

00:16:56.733 --> 00:16:59.539
on policing course two,
but it's never the opposite.

00:16:59.605 --> 00:17:03.045
This has only deepened the rift
with no end in sight,

00:17:03.112 --> 00:17:04.949
which is not acceptable.

00:17:05.016 --> 00:17:08.690
This is overt discrimination
and I simply won't allow it.

00:17:08.757 --> 00:17:09.792
[gasps]

00:17:10.493 --> 00:17:11.495
[stammers]

00:17:12.497 --> 00:17:14.502
President,
as vice president,

00:17:14.569 --> 00:17:16.438
I officially dispute
appointing Tatsuya Shiba

00:17:16.506 --> 00:17:18.008
to the disciplinary committee.

00:17:19.377 --> 00:17:22.483
A course two who lacks power
would be in over his head.

00:17:22.551 --> 00:17:23.787
‐ Just a minute!
‐ [grunts]

00:17:23.853 --> 00:17:24.822
[gasps]

00:17:24.889 --> 00:17:26.258
Yes, it's true,

00:17:26.325 --> 00:17:28.930
that my brother's practical
test scores were sub par,

00:17:28.997 --> 00:17:32.036
but it was only because
his skills were incompatible

00:17:32.103 --> 00:17:33.673
with the method of assessment.

00:17:33.740 --> 00:17:37.113
[Miyuki] In actual battle,
my brother would defeat anyone.

00:17:37.848 --> 00:17:38.750
<i>[Gyobu] Miss Shiba,</i>

00:17:38.817 --> 00:17:41.121
a magician must
recognize everything

00:17:41.188 --> 00:17:43.125
for what it really is
and do so quickly,

00:17:43.192 --> 00:17:44.929
calmly,
and rationally.

00:17:45.463 --> 00:17:47.935
Because we have the power
to make the impossible possible,

00:17:48.002 --> 00:17:50.306
we are expected
to train ourselves rigorously

00:17:50.373 --> 00:17:52.110
in order to maintain
full integrity

00:17:52.176 --> 00:17:54.281
and serve the greater
public interest.

00:17:54.615 --> 00:17:57.253
An aspiring magician
cannot allow her judgment

00:17:57.320 --> 00:17:58.990
to be clouded by rank nepotism.

00:17:59.057 --> 00:18:00.326
Pardon my bluntness,

00:18:00.393 --> 00:18:01.996
but my judgment isn't
the least bit clouded.

00:18:02.063 --> 00:18:04.702
With my brother's true gifts
and abilities, he could kick‐‐

00:18:04.769 --> 00:18:06.305
[gasps]

00:18:16.826 --> 00:18:18.429
Vice president Hattori.

00:18:18.495 --> 00:18:19.431
[grunts]

00:18:21.034 --> 00:18:22.671
How about a simulated battle?

00:18:22.738 --> 00:18:23.873
What?

00:18:23.940 --> 00:18:27.080
[all gasping]

00:18:29.050 --> 00:18:31.088
Wow, the sheer arrogance.

00:18:31.923 --> 00:18:33.425
You, a mere reserve!

00:18:33.827 --> 00:18:34.729
[scoffs]

00:18:34.795 --> 00:18:36.465
[Gyobu] What
are you smirking at?

00:18:37.333 --> 00:18:40.974
Well, it's just that you said it
only moments ago.

00:18:41.509 --> 00:18:44.047
[Tatsuya] Magicians must strive
to remain calm and cool,

00:18:44.114 --> 00:18:45.751
remember?
‐ [grunts]

00:18:46.184 --> 00:18:47.286
You see,

00:18:47.353 --> 00:18:49.190
I want no part
of this committee,

00:18:49.257 --> 00:18:51.663
but if I'm going to prove
my sister's judgment

00:18:51.729 --> 00:18:54.434
is pure and clear,
I have no choice.

00:18:55.102 --> 00:18:57.240
Have it your way,
but fair warning.

00:18:57.307 --> 00:18:59.411
I'm about to show you just
how much you need

00:18:59.477 --> 00:19:00.847
to learn your place here.

00:19:04.154 --> 00:19:07.060
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:19:07.126 --> 00:19:09.732
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:19:09.799 --> 00:19:11.268
I'm so sorry, brother.

00:19:12.738 --> 00:19:14.809
There's nothing
to be sorry about.

00:19:14.875 --> 00:19:18.082
But once again
I've caused trouble for you

00:19:18.148 --> 00:19:19.484
and it's all my fault.

00:19:20.019 --> 00:19:21.355
[exhales]

00:19:23.626 --> 00:19:24.562
[gasps]

00:19:26.264 --> 00:19:28.770
Like I told you
at the ceremony...

00:19:29.204 --> 00:19:31.008
You're always getting angry
on my behalf

00:19:31.074 --> 00:19:32.811
since I can't get angry myself.

00:19:33.212 --> 00:19:34.715
And it picks me up every time.

00:19:36.118 --> 00:19:37.487
[gasps]

00:19:39.324 --> 00:19:41.863
So you don't need
to say you're sorry.

00:19:42.296 --> 00:19:44.568
I know a much more
fitting phrase right now.

00:19:45.269 --> 00:19:46.773
[sniffles]

00:19:46.839 --> 00:19:47.941
[whimpers]

00:19:48.008 --> 00:19:49.411
Yes.

00:19:50.046 --> 00:19:51.348
[Miyuki] I wish you good luck.

00:19:59.732 --> 00:20:01.301
[Tatsuya] Sorry for the wait.

00:20:03.338 --> 00:20:06.846
So do you always carry multiple
storage devices around with you?

00:20:06.913 --> 00:20:08.115
[Tatsuya] Yes,

00:20:08.182 --> 00:20:10.019
since I lack
the processing skills

00:20:10.086 --> 00:20:11.956
to master a general CAD.

00:20:12.925 --> 00:20:14.294
[scoffs]

00:20:23.245 --> 00:20:25.015
Let's go over the rules.

00:20:25.717 --> 00:20:27.487
[Mari] Spells that are known
to be fatal

00:20:27.554 --> 00:20:30.226
as well as those that cause
your opponent irreparable damage

00:20:30.292 --> 00:20:31.963
are expressly forbidden.

00:20:32.564 --> 00:20:35.102
And direct attacks should
never cause your opponent

00:20:35.169 --> 00:20:36.973
anything more than a sprain.

00:20:37.340 --> 00:20:38.977
Weapons are prohibited.

00:20:39.512 --> 00:20:41.448
Bare‐handed attacks
are permitted.

00:20:41.916 --> 00:20:44.789
The winner will be declared
either when a party concedes

00:20:44.855 --> 00:20:47.561
or when the referee determines
a party cannot continue.

00:20:47.995 --> 00:20:50.166
I will respond
to any infractions with force

00:20:50.232 --> 00:20:51.468
so be prepared.

00:20:51.869 --> 00:20:53.238
That is all.

00:20:53.673 --> 00:20:55.544
<i>[Gyobu] In a battle</i>
<i>between magicians,</i>

00:20:55.610 --> 00:20:57.881
<i>whoever strikes first</i>
<i>with a spell wins.</i>

00:20:57.948 --> 00:21:00.587
<i>Also, a Bloom would never lose</i>
<i>to a Weed,</i>

00:21:00.654 --> 00:21:01.789
<i>thanks to the speed</i>

00:21:01.856 --> 00:21:03.927
<i>of his CAD‐based</i>
<i>spell activation.</i>

00:21:05.129 --> 00:21:06.264
<i>Not only that,</i>

00:21:06.331 --> 00:21:07.734
<i>but I hear even for a Weed</i>

00:21:07.801 --> 00:21:09.939
<i>my rival's practical skills</i>
<i>are weak,</i>

00:21:10.005 --> 00:21:11.909
<i>which means</i>
<i>I've already won before</i>

00:21:11.976 --> 00:21:13.278
<i>the match starts.</i>

00:21:15.316 --> 00:21:16.619
<i>And right after it does,</i>

00:21:16.686 --> 00:21:18.590
<i>I'm going to launch</i>
<i>a simple speed‐oriented</i>

00:21:18.656 --> 00:21:20.527
<i>activation sequence</i>
<i>and make sure it's complete</i>

00:21:20.594 --> 00:21:23.098
<i>before Shiba's.</i>
<i>I know.</i>

00:21:23.165 --> 00:21:25.236
<i>I'll cast</i>
<i>an essential singularity‐type</i>

00:21:25.302 --> 00:21:26.572
<i>movement spell.</i>

00:21:28.208 --> 00:21:31.348
<i>It'll knock his sorry ass back</i>
<i>a good ten meters,</i>

00:21:31.414 --> 00:21:32.985
<i>and the shock</i>
<i>will render him unfit</i>

00:21:33.051 --> 00:21:34.287
<i>for battle.</i>

00:21:38.530 --> 00:21:40.867
<i>Then victory will be mine.</i>

00:21:45.042 --> 00:21:46.278
Are you ready?

00:21:50.821 --> 00:21:51.856
Begin!

00:21:51.923 --> 00:21:53.560
[device beeping]

00:21:53.626 --> 00:21:54.595
[grunts]

00:21:56.131 --> 00:22:01.676
[gasping]

00:22:07.086 --> 00:22:09.792
[all gasping]

00:22:09.859 --> 00:22:11.328
[gasps]

00:22:16.672 --> 00:22:18.510
[stammers and gasps]

00:22:19.377 --> 00:22:21.716
The winner is Tatsuya Shiba.

00:22:21.782 --> 00:22:24.889
<i>[ELISA's "Millenario"]</i>

00:22:24.955 --> 00:22:28.796
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:22:28.863 --> 00:22:31.969
<i>[ELISA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:22:32.036 --> 00:22:38.950
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:23:02.263 --> 00:23:08.576
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:23:08.643 --> 00:23:11.348
<i>♪♪ Shape of my love ♪♪</i>

00:23:11.414 --> 00:23:14.287
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

00:23:14.354 --> 00:23:21.234
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:23:21.301 --> 00:23:23.773
<i>♪♪ Eternal song ♪♪</i>

00:23:23.840 --> 00:23:26.946
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

00:23:27.013 --> 00:23:33.960
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

